summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 33063, entitled: "An ordinance providing for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of California Avenue from West Webster Street to Upper Court, and of West Webster Street from California Avenue and 44th Avenue Southwest; providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor; and providing that the cost of said improvement shall be paid by special assessment upon the property specially benefited in the manner provided by law", approved May 7, 1914.
